result.execSummary:
The defendant Denasia N Danzy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Harboring/Aiding a Felon, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.47(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Mary Garvin Guimont in court, defendant Denasia N Danzy not in court, in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for decision.  For reasons stated on the record, the Court GRANTS the defense motion for expungement.  Upon successful completion of the sentence Court will consider motion for expungement.

Defendant Denasia N Danzy in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Denasia N Danzy in custody.  Irene Elizabeth Parthum appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  ENTRY MADE WITHOUT COURT FILE.
Court will consider defense motion for expungement.  Briefing schedule as follows: Defense brief due 11/19/2014, State's response due 12/10/2014.  Case adjourned for decision in Branch 22.

Defendant Denasia N Danzy in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Denasia N Danzy in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: MPD Detective Eric Draeger.

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 YEARS with 1 day credit CONCURRENT to any other sentence; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.

Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and the Earned Release program.  

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in case# 13CF5268 (which was dismissed but read in for the purpose of sentencing) the amount of $442.40 payble to Kent O joint and several with Malik Hill (case# 14CF236);
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  No cash bail on deposit.
-  The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm. 
Court advised defendant of her right to seek postconviction relief.
Court advised defendant that she may not vote until her civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Denasia N Danzy in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Denasia N Danzy in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.

AS TO COUNTS 2 and 3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders Counts 2 and 3 DISMISSED and read-in for purposes of sentencing.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored.  Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department pending sentencing.
